		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I meant tanking advantages, battleblade.&nbsp; The reason it's absurd to think that a warrior can, and always has tanked better than a knight in all situations is due to the topic of this thread- downward scaling tools.&nbsp; It's <i>always </i>been true that at some point, due to downward scaling abilities, a knight's self healing and stunning will exceed a warrior's mitigation.&nbsp; In fact, on stunnable content, pallies have long been far and away the best tank.&nbsp; And due to the utter uselessness of stuns on much modern content, pallies probably need the most work of any of the tank classes (ie, stuns that can be partially mitigated, keeping stun damage reduction to a sane level, but still allow it as a viable technique for avoiding damage).<br><br>And you also have advantages that I can't touch with any amount of gear.<br><br>Warriors could certainly use some tweaks at this point.&nbsp; I'm just tired of some of the absurd misconceptions about my class that some people spread here.&nbsp; If it wasn't for that, I wouldn't even bother to post on this forum.<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
