			<div></div><p>BB, warriors had -1di added later and they had the defensive abilities added later because before that they were a class you played till level 20 or so to get the hang of EQ, then droped in favor of a real class. There was good reason they were considered a beginners class, they had decent hps and could live long enough for noobs to figure out where things were and then run to the zone. </p><p>Why do you think they had a 5% xp bonus? So peeps could level quickly, get the hang of it, and move to something else. They have beewn tweeking the game for the last several expansions to keep the three tanks all viable in any group situation. Groups don't have to go ooc and &quot;look for a real tank&quot; because any of the three will work.</p><p>Besides I remember full well groups takeing me as a 'real tank&quot; despite my spiky health because I could agro anything, anywhere at anytime. That agro power made it worth the risk, they just brought an extra healer to help out. Now with agro improvements made to warriors, they improved my tanking ability, imagine that?</p><p>Also the knights never mentioned an avoidance dicsapline that all the other tank classes have, they said avoidance ability all melee have, includeing non tank classes. Now we used to have spells that would make us invunerable for 18 seconds wich was fine, untill they made agro impossible with it. now aside from setting ramp it's pretty useless.</p><p>CoS is not an sk ability nor is it a class discription, it's a way to take advantage of the game in ways that SoE frowns apon, it's why they changed the casting time. Mine takes 5 seconds, everytime. Fear kiteing is useless at level 70, it's not an arguement you can use because most of us here are level 70. Caster mobs don't stop casting on my FD allready. That's why I rarely FD pull, it's a waste of time, I just grab and extra tank and pull two or three.</p><p>I'm not actually a tankmage I'm a  necromatic tank. Elemental magic is the stuff of mages, I use darker arts. I never picked sk so I could not tank, I fully expected to tank and cast right from the start. ( well level 9 is when I got my first spell, I was a base tank until then) Sure, fear kiteing was cool, but how many raids or high end instance group zones allow me to employ that? Zip, zero, nadda, none. Can't FD pull well cause caster mobs never stop casting, bards and monks are multiple times better at it anyhow. So basically in those settings I'm a tank,  with tanking spells. Spells that cause agro, take ac, take attack, debuff the mobs and increase my health through lifetaps.</p><p> </p>	
