		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><div></div>Sharbreena,<br>
<br>
You ought to check again. My hunting zones included the most brutal
mobs in zones starting with Griffins at Inn 2 and included all kinds of
giants - ice giants, fire giants, hill giants , named (I killed Xicotyl
so may times for Paladins it was disgusting) to Warirors finally
getting their Class Defining defensive disciplines and abilities that
should not have been shared but were and tanking Cappy, to Jords
sreatching all the way to GoD post adjustment and dare I say even OoW -
there were very few Knights that took on Shadowhunter and Warfiend as
early in groups.<br>
<br>
These were mobs that when first encountered munched Knights, content
that started out as raid content or at least two group encounters and
becane doable by group, epic encounters, etc.<br>
<br>I realize you spent a lot of time Fear Kiting and may not know, but pretending that this content did not exist, that Knights did not react
to it by requesting that Defensive not be applicable to group content,
and that SoE did not design content to be easily Knight tankable and
insure that in none of it would Defensive be required to succeed (which
SoE explicitly stated it had done) is beyond simple revisionism, its
prevarication.<br>
<br>
"...I suspect they will continue with the trend they started with the "3 viable tanks" world view they have."<br>
I suspect that they came to understand that if Knights could tank the
content as readily as Warriors, that gave Knights huge advantage in
ancillary abilities that were so powerful they amounted to full
secondary roles. After pretending that this was not the case, they
finally were faced with other information:<br>
<br>
1. As designers, they had never concieved of Warriors having much
outside of their class capability. One designer admitted he didn't
understand why Warriors receive weapons that proced slow, snare, stun,
etc. and has not been introducing very many upgrades to them for that
reason.<br>
<br>
Despite realizing group friendly abilities were an issue for Warriors,
thay abandoned the Phase 2 Melee Update and the Special Openings system
and created Beserkers insted.<br>
<br>
2. Warriors didn't sign up to be hybrids and don't want to be hybrids.
They certaily don't want their utility to be inferior random crap
rather than having a powerful pocket cleric or being a Monk in plate
armor. We chose the Warrior class to be a 100% tank and tanking superiority.<br>
<br>
3. Knights are rabidly opposed to Warriors getting utility, or at least
useful utility - they concider it their Free Bonus, like horses. With
Warriors already having snare whips, right click items, amd the ability
to kill outright lower con runners there was STILL resistance to
conceeding that Warriors should be able to stop runners and the
eventual addition of Call of Challange.<br>
<br>
That leaves us all in a tight spot.<br>
<br>
SoE must include content hard enough that some Knights whine "It's tooo
haaaaard!!" otherwise the central defining Warrior distinguishing
characteristic becomes raid only - something they have not done with
20k+ slay, Paladin clerical abilities, or SK pulling. Even where we are now I'd suggest that all non-raiding Warirors just quit and roll another class or find another game - there's no place for you in EQ.<br>
<br>
They will likely continue to erode the value of Knight ancillary
abilities (less stunable content, healing potions, corpse summoning at
the guild hall) and share them.<br>
<br>
And Warriors will continue to get an additional capability here and there in efect hybridizing us over our stated objections. Should there come a time when Knights and their friends in SoE can legitmately say "You are hybrids in group content Warriors.", we'll have to catalog our abilities and see how they stack up against having a pocket cleric or being a plate monk. I suspect they wil compared poorly and not be in tune with why we chose to play our class.<br>
<br>
All because Knights decided they wanted the advantages of a spellbook,
but they were unwiling to accept that like it or not Warriors are
intended to <u>tank better</u> than paliies and SK's - even in group content.<br>
<br>
I know any number of high level Warriors that no longer play except to
raid. Changes to content, improvements to Knights, the appearance of having upgrades but the reality of not having them (mainhanders, Shiled Block, Shocking Defeince, etc.) have destroyed the
reason they created a Warrior and played them for 6+ years. Since that
was the Knight goal, all I can say is gg Knights and your friends in
content, itemization design, and class *cough* re-envisionment.<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>03-08-2006</span> <span class=time_text>03:17 AM</span>	
		</td></tr>
