			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Don't you see how moronic your statements are, BattleBlade?</P>
<P>When Warrior raid abilities scale upwards and make them preferred group tanks, it's acceptable, no, it's the way it should be.</P>
<P>When Paladin stuns scale upwards and make them preferred group tanks, it's an abomination.... unacceptable.</P>
<P>You're using game mechanics to defend Warrior tanking abilities, and your own delusion as to the lesser role of Knights as defense of your position on stuns.</P>
<P>And you never had a monopoly on "Endurance Fueled Defensive Disciplines" especially since we had Resistant and Fearless since Velious!... what's that?&nbsp; Oh ya, non-mana fueled disciplines?&nbsp; Wait, but why was the endurance system even changed?&nbsp; Because Warrior aggro sucked.</P>
<P>See BB, change happens when there's an imbalance... and unfortunately for you and your fantasy land, it doesn't allow a Warrior to remain as a 'preferred' group tank.&nbsp; Quite the contrary, all Plate tanks are viable tanks,&nbsp;</P>
<P>As much as you want to quote the history of EQ as the 'way it should be'.... you leave out periods of time where Warriors were worthless....&nbsp;Selectively picking and choosing what pieces of history to relate might be eye-opening for some of the noobs that might believe you... but the players know... they know the history of EQ isn't perfect, and that changes were made... and that even Druids, the most uber class in all of original EQ can have their power wean and fluctuate as classes are constantly trying to be balanced.</P>
