		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>So you are saying&nbsp; Warriors should tank hard mobs better than Knights, and then you say that Warriors do tank hard mobs better than Knights.&nbsp; Then W-T-F is the problem?</P>
<P>But nowhere does that imply that we should not be able to tank that content.&nbsp; You seem to be of the belief that there should be this group content designed explicitly for Warriors, shouldn't be the case, and SoE has said that they will make it a point that it will not be the case.&nbsp;</P>
<P>And for the record, we are not equal tank+spellbook as much as you would love to say such.&nbsp; As you have made that statement so many times in the past and then when challenged to take a Knight to tank appropriate content without ever using a spell to prove it, you just pretend to have not read it or something.&nbsp; The challenge is still out there.&nbsp; Take a Paladin from your guild, drag him to DSkeep or ToB and tell him to tank without spells and compare to yourself..... or a SK even.&nbsp; We all know already what the results would be....... so much for your propaganda of Knights being equal+spellbook.&nbsp; It is our spells that balance us to tank in groups where we lack the power that Warriors possess.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><p>Message Edited by Cellan on <span class=date_text>03-08-2006</span> <span class=time_text>05:29 AM</span>	
